Text.Value: You gonna cane 'em or what? Time those rothé got to work.
*You remember blacksmiths speaking of it in hushed awe - the hardest substance known to exist, used for the finest weapons and armour.*
Gh'rack - you knew I'd rile them up. I'll split you from head to hole for this!
NgghhHA!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Skarjall cracks the cane at the rothe with his last NggghHA!
EditorData.NodeContext: Cracks a whip at his beast of burden.
EditorData.SFXTags: Whip hit rothe/ Rothe in pain
EditorData.VFXTags: Dust on Cane Impact on Rother VFX (WilsonLee)

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The duergar canes the rothe and they go into a frenzy, ready to attack everyone near.
EditorData.SFXTags: Bg SFX on whipping (WilsonLee)/ Angry Rothe noise & hoofs stomping on ground

Text.Value: There's an adamantine forge back there, sure as shittin'.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Skarjall takes out his weapon and enters combat stance.
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX for pulling out his weapon (WilsonLee)

Text.Value: *Your eye finds the source of the gleam: a small mote of black metal. Adamantine.*

EditorData.VFXTags: a metal shine VFX on the adamantine (WilsonLee)

Text.Value: Thanks for the tip. Once you're dead, I'll have that forge to myself.
A brute? Is that what you see?
Now get to the canin', before I thrash you instead.
Shit. Sooner give a lurker a lickjob.
What's behind the rubble?
Shouldn't be trouble for a brute like you.
Hold your tongue. Those rothé are ready to blow - and you'll be lighting the fuse.
Adamantine is precious, jargh. And I'm not the sharing type.
Show the animals some respect. Then you may get results.
Adamantine. Stuff's no joke. Stronger than steel, rarer than mithral. It ain't mined - it's made.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: TASKMASTER SKARJALL pulls a small rock of admanatine from his rear pocket and holds it out. He then puts it back in his pocket.
EditorData.VFXTags: a metal shine VFX on the adamantine (WilsonLee)

Text.Value: Drugnin' hoon. I'll split you from head to hole!
You're after adamantine? That stuff's too fine for your lot. Best you stick to scrap iron.
Think if you respect a turd it'll smell any sweeter? Waste of bloody time.
Sure as shittin' you could deal with some stubborn rothe. Go on, get 'em moving.
Adamantine. Bet we're near the forge. Wonder if I could melt that stuff...
I saw it too - adamantine. The forge is behind the rubble. And the duergar mean to lay claim to it.
Watch it - take the cane to those beasts again and this standoff turns to slaughter.
Well look here - Nere's killer in the flesh. Make yourself useful, grab a cane and whip these drugnin' beasts into shape.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hoon = outsider. Dorn = friend. Urop (YUR-op) - slave.

Text.Value: You got no need to know, and I got no need to tell. So get to caning, or to leaving.
*A slight glint catches your eye.*
Another lick of the cane and those rothés are going on a rampage.
You'll be feeling even worse in a moment.
Best if you stop whinging and get those whiskers trimmed.
Oh aye, maybe say pretty please as well? Throw in a curtsy? Don't be soft.
Gettin' cramps in my arm from trying to whip the drugnin' beasts back to work.
Rest your arm. I'll put these beasts to work.
You want my help? Then you will tell me what's back there.
Please. Are you so feeble you can't deliver a single lash?
Let's see what I can do.
Don't get any smart ideas - that forge is clan property. But get the beasts moving and I'll toss some coin your way.
You want to thrash me? Go on, then.
Leave.
You what, now?
That rubble needs clearing, and my patience is hanging on by an arse whisker.
Drugh. Should'a told you to piss off when I had the chance.

EditorData.stateContext: Taskmaster Skarjall is holding cane in his hand for entirety of dialogue

Text.Value: A duergar asking a dwarf for help? Never thought I'd see the day.
Leave it to me. I'll show these deep rothé who's in charge.
Adamantine. That forge must be within spitting distance.
Leave.
I almost feel bad about this.
You want to access the forge, is that it? I've already been there.
You got your orders. I'm not taking one more whack.
I know what you're after. There's adamantine back there, isn't there?
Out of my way. I'll take care of the rothé.
Just because we don't waste time prettifying things doesn't mean we can't make use of good ore.
Let 'em clear the rubble. Then you'll get what's coming to you.
A brute? Is that what you see?
Fine. Look at this.
Not enough caning for my tastes, but you got the job done.

EditorData.logicalname: Player clicks after way is clear before auto dialogue starts

Text.Value: What in the hells? I helped you, and now you want me dead?
If he winds up, I'm gonna snap his neck - if the rothé don't stomp his lights out first.
There's no denying the blood-call. And there's no shame in it. Now go on, brute, and get these beasts moving.
Don't think I won't thrash you harder than the rothé.
What's behind the rubble, anyway?
Just as well, perhaps. Beat anything for long enough and it'll snap.
How about you stop making messes? Grab a cane and whip these beasts into shape.
Stuff's no joke. Stronger than steel, rarer than mithral. It ain't mined - it's made.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: TASKMASTER SKARJALL sighs, pulls a rock of admanatine from his rear pocket,  and holds it out. About the size and shape of a small rock. He then puts it back in his pocket.
EditorData.VFXTags: a metal shine VFX on the adamantine (WilsonLee)

Text.Value: Just splittin' then? Suit your damn self.
Do your own dirty work.
Go on, get 'em moving.
Damned right I do.
What in the hells are you turning on me for?
I saw you scuttling over, urop. Grab a cane and whip the beasts into shape.
You - grab a cane and whip these drugnin' beasts into shape.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hoon = outsider. Dorn = friend. Urop (YUR-op) - slave.

Text.Value: Grab a cane and get these rothé moving!
Adamantine. We must be nearing the forge.
Sure as shittin'. One look from you'd send half this place runnin'. Bloody handy, that.
Get to caning, or to leaving.
Get to caning or to leaving, hoon.
Focus on the glint.
Go on, then - light a fire under the buggers.
Well lookie there - and not one crack of the cane.
And it sounds like your arse wants for a lashing, the way you talk out of it.

EditorData.stateContext: Skarjall is in combat stance, ready to attack.

Text.Value: You saw it too? The fabled adamantine forge is around the bend. We just have a few snags to untangle.
Just you wait for what happens next.
Almost sounds like you're asking for help, if I ignore your tone.
You want me to cane these poor beasts?
Call on the parasite, connect with the taskmaster. What does he seek?
Perhaps you should just try asking them instead.
*The glint fades before your eye finds its source.*
You can't keep me from the forge - I've already found it.
Sure as shittin'. That orc blood makes you damn near feral.
Shit. You calling me weak, jargh?
Something's spooked the dumbshits. So stop your jawin', and get to workin'.
Well would you look at that. The forge can't be far now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Notices a glittering spot of precious metal

Text.Value: If you ain't helping, piss off.
You want my help? Then you will tell me what's back there.
*You see only the most mundane of rocks and minerals.*
Sounds like your problem. Figure it out yourself.
Examine the rubble for anything unusual.
Leave.
Keep this between us or you'll never see another day - got it?
Leave.
I know these creatures well. You should give them another lash of the cane.
You're one of Nere's, eh? Don't go bursting those head-veins - I ain't joined your bat-brained cult.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player tries to mindmeld with the taskmaster but fails.

Text.Value: There's an adamantine forge back there, jargh. And I'm not the sharing type.
Fool. He should've used the threat of the cane over the cane itself. Now those beasts are ready to charge.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disdainful. A heavy-handed duergar foreman's been mistreating his beasts of burden.

Text.Value: Volunteering, are you? Well we ain't getting paid to flirt. Might not get paid at all, with this mess.

Synopsis: The taskmaster is another cruel duergar. He is whipping several pack animals to clear out some rubble, but his arm is tired and asks you to step in. You might discover they want the rubble cleared because a valuable forge can be found behind it. If you convince the beasts to break through, he attacks you because he doesn't want to share the wealth.
